You can also just use lme4::glmer() directly. Except for model="CM.EL", that is what rma.glmm() uses in the background by default. Other package options are glmmTMB and GLMMadaptive. This can handle multilevel structures. On the other hand, if the same participants were measured on multiple dichotomous response variables (or at multiple time points), then things are more tricky, since in principle one would need the IPD data to model this correctly. If one just has the aggregated counts for each response variable, then RVE might work (either with a multilevel logistic model or GEE).

Best,
Wolfgang

